  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Panama and Costa Rica: Strengthening Government Capacities to Respond to Protection Needs in Flows of Vulnerable Migrants Crossing Borders</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on the favorable position of IOM in Costa Rica and Panama in leading and coordinating inter-agency efforts to address migratory issues, as well as with government counterparts, this project will support national and local governments to address factors described in the Crisis Response Plan for Large Movements of Highly Vulnerable Migrants in the Americas under section 1C. It also aims to address the health and protection concerns of migrants who transit the Panama-Costa Rica border in vulnerable and/or deteriorated health conditions, or who have been victims of violence or are potential victims of violence en route. The project will contribute to strengthening Governments capacity to ensure proper access to basic services (health, psychological support, shelter, social services, and others, as needed), information, and dignified treatment, setting a positive precedent of bi-national collaboration in the establishment of proper response protocols for vulnerable migrants crossing borders.</narrative>
  </description>
